474
00:33:46,690 --> 00:33:49,158
She found this great new place,
nobody knows about it.

475
00:33:49,226 --> 00:33:51,558
You should just meet her there.
Here's the address.

476
00:33:51,695 --> 00:33:56,155
[Penny] Oh, I know this place.
I used to come here when I was a kid.

477
00:33:56,233 --> 00:33:59,566
- Isn't it beautiful?
- But it isn't a restaurant, is it?

478
00:33:59,636 --> 00:34:02,264
[Milo] Nah, it's full of plants
and flowers and stuff.

479
00:34:02,339 --> 00:34:06,241
You know what? I broke into this joint.
Mid-50s, Valentine's Day.

480
00:34:06,310 --> 00:34:08,244
My girlfriend needed flowers.

481
00:34:08,312 --> 00:34:11,543
[Harrison] At least it's not crowded.
I hate it when people walk through me.

482
00:34:11,615 --> 00:34:13,879
- Wow!
- [Milo] It depends on who it is.

483
00:34:13,951 --> 00:34:16,545
[Harrison] That's another place
where we're different, Milo.

484
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:20,283
I always considered it
an invasion of my personal space.

485
00:34:22,793 --> 00:34:25,353
[Thomas]
Sorry I'm late, honey.

486
00:34:27,998 --> 00:34:31,434
- God, how did you get them
to let you use this place?
- They owe me.

487
00:34:31,502 --> 00:34:35,131
- Yeah?
- Yeah, I did the P.R.
For their fund-raiser last year.

488
00:34:35,205 --> 00:34:37,469
Mmm.

489
00:34:43,747 --> 00:34:46,511
Stop it with your
"What's she getting me into?" look.

490
00:34:46,583 --> 00:34:49,279
Oh, come on, Anne. You know,
you're... you're doing something here.

491
00:34:49,353 --> 00:34:51,446
Yeah, lunch.

492
00:34:53,123 --> 00:34:56,058
Well, it looks good.

493
00:34:56,126 --> 00:34:59,289
[Clears Throat, Sighs]

494
00:34:59,363 --> 00:35:03,959
- Ahhh, Barbados.
- Right. Very good.

495
00:35:04,034 --> 00:35:07,162
Yeah, it was the closest
I could come on my lunch break.

496
00:35:07,237 --> 00:35:10,536
[Sighs]
So... relax, eat.

497
00:35:11,909 --> 00:35:14,503
I'm just trying to get us
out of our routine.

498
00:35:17,314 --> 00:35:19,748
- Barbados?
- Where they first met.

499
00:35:19,817 --> 00:35:21,808
Don't you remember anything?

500
00:35:24,054 --> 00:35:28,957
I like this girl. Much better
than little Miss "Look At My Butt.

501
00:35:29,026 --> 00:35:31,756
- Everybody, Thomas, look at my butt."
- [Men Laughing]

502
00:35:31,829 --> 00:35:35,595
What about the other one with the legs?
I'm telling you...

503
00:35:35,666 --> 00:35:38,066
this is the one.

504
00:35:38,135 --> 00:35:41,798
You don't think she's getting
fed up with him already, do you?

505
00:35:41,872 --> 00:35:45,467
Just because we do the same thing over
and over again doesn't, you know...

506
00:35:45,542 --> 00:35:47,567
You call that routine?

507
00:35:47,644 --> 00:35:52,377
Well, yeah, sure, anybody would.
I mean, so would... my parents.

508
00:35:52,449 --> 00:35:54,383
- Speaking of my parents,
- Uh-huh?

509
00:35:54,451 --> 00:35:57,852
They're gonna be in town tomorrow night,
and we'd love you to stop by.

510
00:35:57,921 --> 00:36:02,449
- It's no big deal. If you're around.
- Uh-huh.

511
00:36:02,526 --> 00:36:05,290
Bingo. Thirty seconds,
he's out of here.

512
00:36:05,362 --> 00:36:08,388
No! It's high time
he should meet her parents.

513
00:36:08,465 --> 00:36:10,865
Oh, God.
The parent moment, right?

514
00:36:10,934 --> 00:36:14,836
Come on, Thomas. She's not gonna
wait around forever. Don't blow it.

515
00:36:14,905 --> 00:36:18,397
- Marry her, don't marry her.
- Phone me when it's over.

516
00:36:18,475 --> 00:36:20,841
Okay, the parent moment.

517
00:36:23,380 --> 00:36:27,111
I don't have any problem
with meeting your parents.

518
00:36:27,184 --> 00:36:29,709
- At some point.
- "At some point"?

519
00:36:29,786 --> 00:36:32,277
God, you know,
listen to you.

520
00:36:32,356 --> 00:36:36,383
Any time things get remotely
serious, you start...

521
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:38,553
I don't know,
wiggling around.

522
00:36:40,697 --> 00:36:42,631
Hmm?

523
00:36:42,699 --> 00:36:45,600
I thought you liked it
when I wiggled around.

524
00:36:45,669 --> 00:36:48,263
God, where did I go wrong?

525
00:36:48,338 --> 00:36:51,705
Guy likes to play the field,
you know. Takes after me.

526
00:36:51,775 --> 00:36:54,209
A baboon in heat
takes after you.

527
00:36:54,278 --> 00:36:56,906
[Laughing]
Oh, Julia, you're killin' me.

528
00:36:56,980 --> 00:36:59,716
[Laughs]

529
00:36:59,849 --> 00:37:03,945
You're killin' me. Oh, yeah,
I'm already dead. I forgot.

530
00:37:04,020 --> 00:37:05,954
Huh.

531
00:37:10,493 --> 00:37:13,121
[Clears Throat]
You guys. Oh.

532
00:37:31,481 --> 00:37:35,941
It... is... time, whoo.

533
00:37:36,018 --> 00:37:39,078
"It's time, whoo"?

534
00:37:39,155 --> 00:37:42,090
All right, all right, all right.
I'm a little late. L...

535
00:37:42,158 --> 00:37:45,150
I should have picked you up
about 15 or 20 years ago,

536
00:37:45,228 --> 00:37:48,459
but, you know, up there,
time's a little relative.

537
00:37:54,470 --> 00:37:56,995
Let's go, dead people.

538
00:38:01,010 --> 00:38:03,444
Time to, you know,
t-t-to go.

539
00:38:04,514 --> 00:38:07,574
[Bus Driver]
I'm taking you onwards.

540
00:38:07,650 --> 00:38:10,141
I know you.

541
00:38:10,219 --> 00:38:12,414
You're the bus driver.

542
00:38:12,488 --> 00:38:15,582
Very good. Now come on.

543
00:38:15,658 --> 00:38:18,149
You're the idiot
that got us all killed.

544
00:38:18,227 --> 00:38:21,685
Yeah.
You lousy bastard.

545
00:38:21,764 --> 00:38:26,428
Because of you,
I've spent the last 30 years...

546
00:38:26,502 --> 00:38:29,437
coolin' my heels
with Mr. Excitement here.

547
00:38:29,505 --> 00:38:32,906
I, I can't get a decent meal,
I can't get a smoke...

548
00:38:32,975 --> 00:38:36,638
and especially,
I can't get laid.

549
00:38:36,712 --> 00:38:39,237
You've turned me
into a goddamn monk!

550
00:38:39,315 --> 00:38:42,113
Hey, back off!
I died in that crash too.

551
00:38:42,185 --> 00:38:44,619
We are so sorry.

552
00:38:44,687 --> 00:38:47,281
Aren't you even gonna
apologize for what you did?

553
00:38:47,356 --> 00:38:51,656
Well, I-I'm doin' penance. I'm drivin'
this bus around for the next 500 years.

554
00:38:51,727 --> 00:38:53,752
Believe me, I'm sorry.

555
00:38:53,830 --> 00:38:58,062
- It's not like they gave me
the opportunities that you got.
- Opportunities?

556
00:38:58,134 --> 00:39:02,901
- For what?
- We know we're not dead.
We know we're not alive.

557
00:39:02,972 --> 00:39:07,170
We know we're not there.
For that matter, we're not here.

558
00:39:07,243 --> 00:39:09,973
We're... what?

559
00:39:10,046 --> 00:39:12,810
- What? What, what?
- What?

560
00:39:12,882 --> 00:39:15,817
What, what is... What is this?
What am I, in the Twilight Zone here?

561
00:39:15,885 --> 00:39:20,322
I'm talking about the opportunity
to resolve your lives.

562
00:39:22,692 --> 00:39:27,720
You know, you get to do the one thing
you would've done before you died...

563
00:39:27,797 --> 00:39:31,358
except you didn't get to do it
on account of some guy...

564
00:39:31,434 --> 00:39:35,268
unintentionally cut your lives
a little... short.

565
00:39:35,338 --> 00:39:40,139
We haven't done anything.
We haven't resolved anything!

566
00:39:40,209 --> 00:39:42,507
You're joking.

567
00:39:44,380 --> 00:39:46,541
I mean, you were told
about this?

568
00:39:46,616 --> 00:39:51,485
The angel, he came down, he explained
it to you? That, that you would...

569
00:39:54,824 --> 00:39:58,487
Okay, hold it.
A-all right, hold it.

570
00:39:58,561 --> 00:40:01,553
All right, back off, back off.
All right, all right! Okay.

571
00:40:02,632 --> 00:40:06,033
[Whispering]

572
00:40:06,102 --> 00:40:09,299
[Stammering] Y-You've been hangin'
around in Limboville there...

573
00:40:09,372 --> 00:40:12,341
since the '50s
just wonderin' what gives?

574
00:40:13,843 --> 00:40:16,641
[Sighs]

575
00:40:16,712 --> 00:40:18,839
Well, you see, what you're
supposed to have done...

576
00:40:18,915 --> 00:40:22,373
is to take care of the one thing that
would have made your lives complete.

577
00:40:22,451 --> 00:40:25,284
You know, I mean I'm not talkin'
about makin' a million dollars,

578
00:40:25,354 --> 00:40:28,551
- or shackin' up with some
pinup girl or something.
- Shackin' up with some pinup...

579
00:40:28,624 --> 00:40:30,558
- Shut up!
- Shut up!

580
00:40:30,626 --> 00:40:32,890
Well, how in the world are we
supposed to do that? We're spirits.

581
00:40:32,962 --> 00:40:34,987
We can't make a phone call.
We can't...

582
00:40:35,064 --> 00:40:38,124
Punch some bus driver
in the chops.

583
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:40,498
Your corporeal being.

584
00:40:42,271 --> 00:40:45,069
You're supposed to use him
as a vehicle.

585
00:40:45,141 --> 00:40:48,008
And if he won't do it, you enter
his body and you make him do it.

586
00:40:48,077 --> 00:40:51,410
- Enter his body?
- We can take him over?

587
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:54,643
Well, that would've
been helpful to know.

588
00:40:54,717 --> 00:40:57,845
I knew there was a reason
for all of this.

589
00:40:57,920 --> 00:41:02,789
Yeah, yeah, sure. It's all part
of the grand scheme of things.

590
00:41:02,858 --> 00:41:07,488
Which is worth diddly if someone
doesn't get his halo down here
and tell you what's goin' on.

591
00:41:07,563 --> 00:41:11,329
Oh, thank God. I thought we were
gonna be stuck here forever!

592
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:13,334
Oh, this is great.

593
00:41:13,402 --> 00:41:15,666
My kids!
I can find out about my kids!

594
00:41:15,738 --> 00:41:18,263
No. No, no. No, no, no.
Wait a second now.

595
00:41:18,341 --> 00:41:20,901
It's too late now. I mean,
I got the bus. It's right here.

596
00:41:20,977 --> 00:41:23,070
What?
You can't take us now.

597
00:41:23,145 --> 00:41:26,376
- Now that we know?
- I gotta take you now. It's time.

598
00:41:26,449 --> 00:41:29,680
And there are new babies on the way,
and you guys are my responsibility.

599
00:41:29,752 --> 00:41:33,279
It's your fault we're here!
I mean, don't you have a conscience?

600
00:41:34,724 --> 00:41:36,749
Everybody gets cancellations.

601
00:41:36,826 --> 00:41:39,351
- Not everybody.
- Oh, come on, please!

602
00:41:39,428 --> 00:41:41,055
Think of your guilt.

603
00:41:41,130 --> 00:41:43,792
Just a little while longer.
You're in charge!

604
00:41:43,866 --> 00:41:45,891
- Look at your schedule.
- Think about your guilt.

605
00:41:45,968 --> 00:41:48,300
All right.
Maybe I can hold off...

606
00:41:48,371 --> 00:41:51,204
until each one of you
is actually needed.

607
00:41:51,273 --> 00:41:53,434
Would you? You would.

608
00:41:53,509 --> 00:41:58,037
I would, but it's not gonna be long,
I'm warning you.

609
00:41:58,114 --> 00:42:02,778
[Groaning] I can't believe
I'm even doing this. It's crazy.

610
00:42:02,852 --> 00:42:05,116
You know, I'm stickin'
my neck out here,

611
00:42:05,187 --> 00:42:08,384
and when I come back for ya,
you better be ready.

612
00:42:08,457 --> 00:42:12,416
- I got first dibs on him.
- [Julia] Oh, no, you don't!

613
00:42:14,363 --> 00:42:16,695
- Hey, Thomas! Hey, man!
- Thomas!

614
00:42:16,766 --> 00:42:20,497
Remember me? It's Milo.
Long time, no see, huh?

615
00:42:20,569 --> 00:42:23,037
...the greatest times of my life.
- Long time, still no see.

616
00:42:23,105 --> 00:42:26,506
[Arguing] You're not
doing it right. Let me try!

617
00:42:26,575 --> 00:42:31,012
- [Arguing Continues]
- When we met, you had this... spark.

618
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:33,014
- Sure.
- What is she talking about?

619
00:42:33,082 --> 00:42:35,277
- I'm just trying to bring that back.
- Thomas, can you hear us?

620
00:42:35,351 --> 00:42:38,081
- I'll meet your parents tomorrow night.
- We're screwed.

621
00:42:38,154 --> 00:42:40,918
- The guy's brain dead.
- Are you concentrating like we used to?

622
00:42:40,990 --> 00:42:43,481
- [Arguing Continues]
- Yes, I'm concentrating!

623
00:42:43,559 --> 00:42:48,496
- How are we gonna get through to him?
- We don't just scream at him.

624
00:42:48,564 --> 00:42:51,465
Thomas!
Hey, wake up!

625
00:42:51,534 --> 00:42:53,468
- Milo, shhh.
- [Horn Honks]

626
00:42:53,536 --> 00:42:56,130
- Stop it. Sit down!
- You can't just yell at him.

627
00:42:56,205 --> 00:42:58,833
Come on, we have to concentrate
together like we used to.

628
00:42:58,908 --> 00:43:01,775
It's a lot easier
to disappear than to appear.

629
00:43:01,844 --> 00:43:03,937
Sing "Walk Like A Man."

630
00:43:04,013 --> 00:43:06,914
- "Walk Like A Man"?
- Good idea.

631
00:43:06,982 --> 00:43:11,419
- Concentrate.
- Okay. Okay, okay, concentrate.

632
00:43:11,487 --> 00:43:15,924
Walk like a man
Talk like a man

633
00:43:15,991 --> 00:43:20,519
Walk like a man
my son

634
00:43:20,596 --> 00:43:24,555
No woman's worth
crawling on the earth

635
00:43:24,633 --> 00:43:27,227
- So walk like a...
- This isn't working.

636
00:43:27,303 --> 00:43:32,172
Oooh

637
00:43:32,241 --> 00:43:36,905
[Yelling Together]
Thomas! Thomas!

638
00:43:37,980 --> 00:43:42,349
Thomas, it's me.
It's Milo.

639
00:43:42,418 --> 00:43:44,852
It's not, not the radio.
It's me! [Growls]

640
00:43:44,920 --> 00:43:47,115
[Grunting]

641
00:43:51,393 --> 00:43:53,327
Ohhh!

642
00:43:53,395 --> 00:43:56,262
- Contact.
- Hope he doesn't take this badly.

643
00:43:56,332 --> 00:43:59,324
[Yelling]

644
00:43:59,401 --> 00:44:01,528
[Tires Screeching]

645
00:44:02,605 --> 00:44:04,869
[Indistinct Shouting]

646
00:44:04,974 --> 00:44:09,206
- You yelled at him in a moving car!
- I did not! I was just a bit loud.

647
00:44:09,278 --> 00:44:12,270
You did. You always
yell everything!

648
00:44:12,348 --> 00:44:15,283
It wasn't even my idea, okay?
It was Penny's. She was the one goin'...

649
00:44:15,351 --> 00:44:17,653
As if... Don't try
to blame me, boy.

650
00:44:17,786 --> 00:44:21,153
- How long's he gonna be out?
- Do I look like an anesthesiologist?

651
00:44:21,223 --> 00:44:24,215
- We've lost a whole night already!
- Nice.

652
00:44:25,527 --> 00:44:28,963
[Groaning]

653
00:44:32,701 --> 00:44:36,137
My car. Uhh,
what happened to my car?

654
00:44:36,204 --> 00:44:39,765
- Thomas?
- Ah, he may be a tad upset.

655
00:44:40,842 --> 00:44:43,310
Thomas?
Sweetie pie,

656
00:44:43,378 --> 00:44:45,312
can you hear us?

657
00:44:47,883 --> 00:44:51,250
We're so sorry, Thomas.
Don't worry, you're gonna be okay.

658
00:44:51,319 --> 00:44:54,345
- What have they got me on?
- How are ya?

659
00:44:56,558 --> 00:44:59,857
You just cracked a couple of ribs,
but you're gonna be okay.

660
00:45:06,201 --> 00:45:09,170
- Oh, my God!
- Thomas, it's been a very long time.

661
00:45:09,237 --> 00:45:12,798
We hope you haven't forgotten us.
We really need your help.

662
00:45:12,874 --> 00:45:15,775
[Gasping]

663
00:45:22,184 --> 00:45:25,176
- God, they're back.
- He remembers us!

664
00:45:25,253 --> 00:45:27,721
- [Shouting]
- He remembers us!

665
00:45:27,789 --> 00:45:30,155
The hallucinations are back.

666
00:45:30,225 --> 00:45:33,023
I never thought of us
as hallucinations.

667
00:45:33,095 --> 00:45:35,495
- Me, neither. Where's he going?
- Wait!

668
00:45:35,564 --> 00:45:37,498
- Thomas?
- Where are you going?

669
00:45:37,566 --> 00:45:40,330
- Bathroom down here?
- We finally figured out
what we're supposed to do.

670
00:45:40,402 --> 00:45:42,563
You're supposed to stay
deep, deep in my subconscious.

671
00:45:42,637 --> 00:45:44,571
Don't run away from us!

672
00:45:44,639 --> 00:45:46,698
- [Arguing]
- Don't jabber at him.

673
00:45:46,775 --> 00:45:50,336
[Arguing Continues]

674
00:45:50,412 --> 00:45:52,346
- [Elevator Bell Rings]
- [Indistinct Chattering]

675
00:45:52,414 --> 00:45:55,349
- He's completely ignoring us!
- Pretending he don't know us.

676
00:45:55,417 --> 00:45:58,318
- [Muttering]
- Oh, straitjacket city!
Thomas, you're not crazy!

677
00:45:58,386 --> 00:46:00,320
- We're real, in our way.
- Hi, guys.

678
00:46:00,388 --> 00:46:03,551
He's a lucky one.
He gets visitors.

679
00:46:03,625 --> 00:46:06,025
- Yeah, sure. Yeah.
- I never get visitors.

680
00:46:17,305 --> 00:46:19,239
[P.A.]
Dr. Singer, please call the operator.

681
00:46:19,307 --> 00:46:21,241
Dr. Singer, please call the operator.

682
00:46:21,309 --> 00:46:23,971
[Sirens Wailing]

683
00:46:28,183 --> 00:46:30,378
Hi.

684
